{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":644,"text":"OK, so, confession:"},{"time":2502,"text":"I've always been weirdly\nobsessed with advertising."},{"time":8238,"text":"I remember watching\nSaturday morning cartoons,"},{"time":11330,"text":"paying more attention to the commercials"},{"time":13487,"text":"than to the shows,"},{"time":14818,"text":"trying to figure out how they were trying\nto get inside my head."},{"time":17932,"text":"Ultimately, that led me to my dream job."},{"time":20035,"text":"I became a partner\nat a big New York ad agency."}]},{"cues":[{"time":23337,"text":"But then, all of that suddenly changed\non February 23, 1997,"},{"time":29550,"text":"when my little brother Matt\nwas shot in the head"},{"time":32922,"text":"in a shooting that happened\non the observation deck"},{"time":35771,"text":"of the Empire State Building."},{"time":37911,"text":"Suddenly, my family was thrown\ninto the middle of a nightmare,"},{"time":43097,"text":"being told that my brother\nwas going to die,"},{"time":47251,"text":"actually being given the opportunity\nto say goodbye to him,"},{"time":50951,"text":"then several emergency brain surgeries"},{"time":53325,"text":"and now what's amounted, for Matt,"},{"time":56000,"text":"to a lifetime spent courageously\nrecovering from a traumatic brain injury."},{"time":62270,"text":"He is definitely my hero."}]},{"cues":[{"time":65101,"text":"But as much as (Applause) --\nyeah, deserves it --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":67467,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":72597,"text":"But as much as this tragedy\nwas a nightmare for my family,"},{"time":78224,"text":"I often think about how much worse\nit could have been;"},{"time":80799,"text":"in fact, how much worse\nit is for the 90 families every day"},{"time":85882,"text":"who aren't as fortunate,"},{"time":87786,"text":"who lose loved ones -- brothers,\nsisters, sons, daughters, parents."},{"time":94018,"text":"They don't all make national headlines."},{"time":96543,"text":"In fact, most of them don't."},{"time":98209,"text":"They go largely unnoticed,"},{"time":100305,"text":"in a nation that's kind of come to accept\na disgraceful national epidemic"},{"time":106928,"text":"as some kind of new normal."}]},{"cues":[{"time":110800,"text":"So I quit my job in advertising"},{"time":113170,"text":"to try and do something about\nthis disgraceful national epidemic,"},{"time":118296,"text":"because I came to realize"},{"time":119517,"text":"that the challenges\nto preventing gun violence"},{"time":122654,"text":"are actually the same ones\nthat made me love advertising,"},{"time":126343,"text":"which is to try to figure out\nhow to engage people."},{"time":128850,"text":"Only instead of doing it to sell products,"},{"time":131477,"text":"doing it to save lives."},{"time":133726,"text":"And that comes down to\nfinding common ground,"},{"time":138673,"text":"where what I want overlaps\nwith what you want."},{"time":142706,"text":"And you might be surprised to learn,\nwhen it comes to gun violence,"},{"time":145936,"text":"just how much common ground there is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":148007,"text":"Let's look, for example,\nat people who love to hunt,"},{"time":151016,"text":"a sport enjoyed by millions across the US."},{"time":154222,"text":"It's a proud tradition. Families."},{"time":156886,"text":"In some places,"},{"time":158064,"text":"the first day of hunting season\nis actually a school holiday."},{"time":161821,"text":"What do hunters want?"},{"time":163285,"text":"Well, they want to hunt.\nThey love their guns."},{"time":165657,"text":"They believe deeply"},{"time":166881,"text":"in the Second Amendment right\nto own those guns."},{"time":169397,"text":"But that doesn't mean\nthere isn't common ground."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171700,"text":"In fact, there's a lot of it,"},{"time":173152,"text":"starting with the basic idea\nof keeping guns out of dangerous hands."},{"time":178580,"text":"This isn't about taking\ncertain guns away from all people."},{"time":183418,"text":"It's about keeping all guns\naway from certain people,"},{"time":186318,"text":"and it's the people that, it turns out,\nwe all agree shouldn't have guns:"},{"time":189807,"text":"convicted violent criminals,\ndomestic abusers,"},{"time":192311,"text":"the dangerously mentally ill."},{"time":195205,"text":"We can all appreciate"},{"time":196380,"text":"how Brady background checks\nhave been incredibly effective"},{"time":199311,"text":"in keeping guns\nout of those dangerous hands."},{"time":201603,"text":"In 20 years, Brady background checks\nat federally licensed firearm dealers"},{"time":206034,"text":"have blocked 2.4 million gun sales"},{"time":209823,"text":"to those people that we all agree\nshouldn't have guns."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213463,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":217410,"text":"And whether you love guns or hate guns,\nyou probably also appreciate"},{"time":221631,"text":"that there shouldn't be thousands\nof gun sales every day"},{"time":224831,"text":"at guns shows or online"},{"time":226701,"text":"without those Brady background checks,"},{"time":228584,"text":"just like there shouldn't be two lines\nto get on an airplane --"},{"time":231608,"text":"one with security\nand one with no security."},{"time":234256,"text":"And --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":235431,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":238957,"text":"And the numbers show the overwhelming\nagreement among the American public:"},{"time":242744,"text":"90 percent of Americans support\nexpanding Brady background checks"},{"time":247051,"text":"to all gun sales -- including\n90 percent of Republicans,"},{"time":249709,"text":"more than 80 percent of gun owners,"},{"time":251653,"text":"more than 70 percent of NRA members."},{"time":253929,"text":"This is not a controversial idea."},{"time":255867,"text":"In fact, only six percent\nof the American public disagrees."},{"time":259467,"text":"That's about the percentage\nof the American public"},{"time":261856,"text":"that believes the moon landing was a fake."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264069,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":265458,"text":"And it's also about the percentage\nthat believes the government"},{"time":268454,"text":"is putting mind-controlling technology\nin our TV broadcast signals."},{"time":272437,"text":"That's the extent to which we agree\nabout background checks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275288,"text":"But what about the 300 million guns"},{"time":278860,"text":"already out there in homes across America?"},{"time":281280,"text":"Well first, it's important to realize"},{"time":283074,"text":"that those guns are mostly\nin the hands and homes"},{"time":287436,"text":"of decent, law-abiding people\nlike you and me,"},{"time":290400,"text":"who want what we all want --\nincluding keeping our families safe."},{"time":294695,"text":"In fact, that's why more and more people\nare choosing to own guns."},{"time":298704,"text":"Ten years ago, 42 percent\nof the American public"},{"time":303063,"text":"believed -- incorrectly -- that a gun\nmakes your home safer."},{"time":307364,"text":"Today, that number is 63 percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":311784,"text":"Why?"},{"time":312960,"text":"I kind of hate to say it,"},{"time":314182,"text":"because it gets to the dark\nunderbelly of advertising,"},{"time":316796,"text":"which is if you tell\na big enough lie enough times,"},{"time":319248,"text":"eventually that lie becomes the truth."},{"time":321113,"text":"And that's exactly what's happened here."},{"time":323084,"text":"The corporate gun lobby\nhas spent billions of dollars"},{"time":325650,"text":"blocking the CDC from doing research\ninto the public health epidemic"},{"time":328999,"text":"of gun violence;"},{"time":330684,"text":"blocking pediatricians\nfrom talking to parents"},{"time":332868,"text":"about the dangers of guns in the home;"},{"time":334703,"text":"blocking smart-gun technology\nand other technology"},{"time":337096,"text":"that would prevent kids\nfrom firing parents' guns"},{"time":339791,"text":"and would save lives."},{"time":341812,"text":"They're desperate to hide the truth,"},{"time":344105,"text":"because they view the truth\nas a threat to their bottom line."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348407,"text":"And every day,"},{"time":349592,"text":"people are dying as a result."},{"time":351211,"text":"And a lot of those people are children."},{"time":354108,"text":"Every day in the US,"},{"time":356469,"text":"nine kids are just shot unintentionally."},{"time":360309,"text":"900 children and teens\ntake their own lives every year."},{"time":365476,"text":"And here's the thing:\nthey're almost all with a parent's gun."},{"time":369874,"text":"Even two-thirds of school shootings\nhappen with a gun taken from the home,"},{"time":376259,"text":"including the terrible tragedy"},{"time":377968,"text":"at Sandy Hook."},{"time":379562,"text":"I meet so many of these parents;"},{"time":381549,"text":"it's the most heartbreaking\npart of my job."},{"time":384379,"text":"These are not bad people."},{"time":387476,"text":"They're just living with the unimaginable\nconsequences of a very bad decision,"},{"time":392715,"text":"made based on very bad information"},{"time":395610,"text":"that was put into their minds\nby very bad people,"},{"time":398522,"text":"who know good and well\nthe misery that they're causing,"},{"time":401751,"text":"but just don't care."},{"time":404577,"text":"And the result is a nightmare --"},{"time":407063,"text":"not only for families like mine,"},{"time":409657,"text":"but for, really, at the end\nof the day, all of us."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413472,"text":"But I'm not here to talk\nabout the nightmare of gun violence."},{"time":416410,"text":"I'm here to talk about our dream,\nand it's a dream we all share,"},{"time":419470,"text":"which is the dream\nof a better, safer, future."},{"time":421970,"text":"For my organization,\nfor the Brady Campaign,"},{"time":424696,"text":"that dream is reflected in the bold goal"},{"time":427308,"text":"to cut the number of gun deaths\nin the US in half by 2025."},{"time":432102,"text":"And I hope to leave\nall of you here tonight"},{"time":434628,"text":"with a strong sense of exactly why\nthat dream is so absolutely within reach."},{"time":440525,"text":"Because folks,"},{"time":441915,"text":"for every great movement around the world,"},{"time":444751,"text":"there's a moment\nwhere you can look back and say,"},{"time":447562,"text":"\"That's when things\nreally started to change.\""},{"time":451065,"text":"And I'm here to say"},{"time":452313,"text":"that for the movement\nto end gun violence in America,"},{"time":455258,"text":"that moment is here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":458308,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":463993,"text":"We are so clearly at a tipping point,"},{"time":466898,"text":"because the American public\nhas come together by the millions"},{"time":470033,"text":"like never before,\nbased on that common ground,"},{"time":472271,"text":"to say, \"Enough.\""},{"time":473690,"text":"Enough of the mass shootings\nin malls and movie theaters"},{"time":476921,"text":"and churches and schools."},{"time":478851,"text":"Enough of the daily terror\nof gun violence in homes and streets"},{"time":483768,"text":"that's claimed the lives of women\nand young black men"},{"time":486999,"text":"in staggering proportions."},{"time":488445,"text":"Enough of easy access to guns"},{"time":490252,"text":"by the people that we all agree\nshouldn't have them."},{"time":492752,"text":"And enough of a small group\nof craven politicians"},{"time":495811,"text":"putting the interests\nof the corporate gun lobby"},{"time":498124,"text":"ahead of the people\nthey have been elected to represent."},{"time":501147,"text":"Enough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":502322,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":508500,"text":"And the really exciting thing is,\nit's not just the usual suspects like me"},{"time":512428,"text":"that are saying it anymore."},{"time":513984,"text":"It's so much bigger than that."},{"time":515912,"text":"And if you want proof,"},{"time":517087,"text":"let's start where most conversations\nin the US seem to start --"},{"time":520663,"text":"with Kim Kardashian."}]},{"cues":[{"time":522091,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":523305,"text":"And here's the thing:\nit's not really a joke."},{"time":525448,"text":"I mean, think about when issues change."},{"time":527345,"text":"It's when they go from being\npolitical and advocacy issues"},{"time":530138,"text":"to being part of pop culture,"},{"time":531568,"text":"voices coming from everywhere,\ncelebrities using their platforms,"},{"time":535161,"text":"musicians, athletes."},{"time":536786,"text":"The NBA has come forward."},{"time":538066,"text":"Conservative pundits that you never\nwould have imagined"},{"time":540744,"text":"have come forward."},{"time":541919,"text":"There's real cultural change --"},{"time":543485,"text":"I even hear there's a TED Talk\nabout it this year."},{"time":545875,"text":"That's the extent to which\nthis cultural change is happening."},{"time":550444,"text":"And yes, Kim Kardashian has made\nan unsolicited passionate appeal"},{"time":554396,"text":"to her 35 million Twitter followers"},{"time":557534,"text":"for expanded background checks."}]},{"cues":[{"time":559906,"text":"Let's look at the political elections\nthat are heating up."},{"time":562845,"text":"This used to be the classic\nthird-rail issue for Democrats."},{"time":565726,"text":"Couldn't run from it fast enough."},{"time":567464,"text":"Now candidates are running on it."},{"time":569171,"text":"Some are being forced\nto reverse very bad positions"},{"time":572162,"text":"they defended very comfortably,\nuntil very recently."},{"time":576408,"text":"For somebody like me,"},{"time":578062,"text":"watching people wave around\ntheir negative NRA ratings --"},{"time":583148,"text":"it's almost surreal to watch."},{"time":586391,"text":"We're still outfunded, yes,\nby the corporate gun lobby,"},{"time":590138,"text":"and ultimately that needs to change."},{"time":592531,"text":"But you know what?"},{"time":593716,"text":"We're smarter and we're scrappier,\nand we have the truth on our side."},{"time":598099,"text":"And we're on offense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":599843,"text":"You know, they say that the Internet\ndemocratizes information."},{"time":603277,"text":"Social media and some\nof the organizing tools that plug into it"},{"time":607039,"text":"have democratized activism."},{"time":608936,"text":"It's allowed us to show what 90 percent\nsupport really looks like."},{"time":612327,"text":"Sometimes I think of it --"},{"time":613598,"text":"you know, we're converging\nand attacking instantly by the millions,"},{"time":616859,"text":"kind of like white blood cells."},{"time":618486,"text":"It's enabled us to start to really\nclose -- and this is the bottom line --"},{"time":623069,"text":"close that disgraceful disconnect"},{"time":625299,"text":"between what the American public wants"},{"time":627735,"text":"and what our elected leaders\nare doing about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630006,"text":"Until recently,"},{"time":631554,"text":"the narrative in Congress\nwas that calls from the other side,"},{"time":634830,"text":"from that six percent,"},{"time":636014,"text":"outnumbered calls from our side 10 to one."},{"time":639218,"text":"We're flipping that narrative on its head."},{"time":641281,"text":"After that recent terrible tragedy\nin San Bernardino,"},{"time":643915,"text":"we jammed Congressional switchboards."},{"time":645744,"text":"We put 15,000 calls\ninto Congress in 24 hours."},{"time":651141,"text":"And you know what?"},{"time":652316,"text":"We got a vote on a bill"},{"time":653491,"text":"that nobody thought was going to see\nthe light of day anytime soon."},{"time":656729,"text":"We're seeing real movement\nto repeal some of the most evil,"},{"time":659594,"text":"ugly gun lobby legislation\npassed over the last dark decade."},{"time":664257,"text":"The stranglehold of the gun lobby\nis clearly being broken."},{"time":667188,"text":"We've seen President Obama's\nhistoric executive actions."},{"time":670514,"text":"They don't go all the way,"},{"time":671928,"text":"but they are going to save lives,"},{"time":673539,"text":"because they expand\nBrady background checks"},{"time":675610,"text":"to thousands of gun sales\nthat didn't have them previously."},{"time":679206,"text":"And we're marching across the country --\nwe're not just waiting"},{"time":682238,"text":"for Congress to act; that would almost\nbe the definition of insanity."},{"time":685647,"text":"We're marching across the country,"},{"time":687316,"text":"state by state, marriage-equality style."}]},{"cues":[{"time":689939,"text":"And you know what? We're winning."},{"time":691537,"text":"Congress is almost always\nthe last to wake up and realize"},{"time":695228,"text":"that it's on the wrong side of history."},{"time":697441,"text":"And when they do, it's always\nbecause the American public shakes them."},{"time":701086,"text":"And that's exactly\nwhat we're doing right now,"},{"time":703292,"text":"as we're in this tipping point."}]},{"cues":[{"time":704854,"text":"You know, recently I was flying\ncross-country to give a speech"},{"time":708827,"text":"to a large group like this,\nalthough far less intimidating,"},{"time":712283,"text":"and the woman sitting next to me\nhappened to be binge-watching"},{"time":716048,"text":"one of my all-time favorite\nTV shows, \"Mad Men,\""},{"time":721000,"text":"a period TV show about advertising"},{"time":723238,"text":"in the 1960s."},{"time":725080,"text":"And as I was trying to think\nabout how to end my remarks,"},{"time":728701,"text":"I'd glance up at her screen\nevery now and then,"},{"time":731000,"text":"and it seemed that every time I did,"},{"time":733317,"text":"I'd see somebody smoking\nin an office or around children"},{"time":737666,"text":"or while pregnant or drinking and driving"},{"time":740103,"text":"or driving without seat belts\nor sexually harassing a coworker."}]},{"cues":[{"time":744098,"text":"And ultimately it dawned on me:"},{"time":746496,"text":"what tremendous inspiration"},{"time":747882,"text":"to those of us who have this dream\nto end gun violence."},{"time":751865,"text":"I mean, think about how much\nthe world has changed"},{"time":754460,"text":"in a relatively short period of time,"},{"time":757263,"text":"how all those behaviors that were once\nconsidered commonplace or normal --"},{"time":760920,"text":"some even glamorous or sexy --"},{"time":763161,"text":"have become stigmatized\nin just a generation or two,"},{"time":767292,"text":"once they became conversations\nabout our common ground."},{"time":771799,"text":"That is the magnitude of the change\nwe have the potential to create"},{"time":776637,"text":"around gun violence."}]},{"cues":[{"time":778296,"text":"And that's my dream,"},{"time":779884,"text":"that maybe someday,"},{"time":781376,"text":"some period TV show will depict\nthe terrible nightmare of gun violence,"},{"time":786895,"text":"and a future generation of children\nmight only be able to imagine"},{"time":790293,"text":"how terrible it must have been."}]},{"cues":[{"time":792166,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":793341,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":799079,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":800254,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":801771,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":802946,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}